Right \u8212? I was reframing your claim as ranking-invariance when your actual point is deeper: the {\b unit of analysis} is the orthogroup-as-entity, and sequence-level heterogeneity doesn't propagate into that unit the way it does into alignment. That's the structural advantage of the approach: you sidestep the sequence-level rate heterogeneity problem by not operating on sequences at all. Cleaner framing; I'll hold that.\par
