\li360  1. {\b Domain-architecture coherence}: pull Pfam profiles of each member gene in a group. If \u8805?90% of members share a dominant domain architecture \u8594? likely family. If domains are heterogeneous \u8594? likely functional mix. Easy to compute since annotations_hmms already runs.\par
\par
\li360  2. {\b Orthogroup clustering of members}: for each HGNC group, check how its human members partition across your species70 orthogroups. If they cluster into 1 orthogroup \u8594? tight family. If they cluster into several small orthogroups that are clearly related (sharing a domain) \u8594? superfamily (still valid). If they scatter across many unrelated orthogroups \u8594? functional mix.\par
\par
\li360  3. {\b Cross-reference HGNC group name/description}: regex for telltale functional descriptors like "receptors", "channels", "enzymes" (functional) vs. "family", "superfamily", "subunits" (likely structural family). Not deterministic but can pre-rank for review.\par
